The `SUMIFS` function in Syncfusion WinForms allows you to sum values in a range based on multiple criteria. Here's an example of how to use it in code:

```csharp
using Syncfusion.Calculate;

public double SumValuesBasedOnCriteria(double[] range, string[] criteriaRange1, string[] criteria1, string[] criteriaRange2, string[] criteria2)
{
    CalcEngine engine = new CalcEngine();
    return (double)engine.Evaluate("=SUMIFS(" + string.Join(",", range) + ", " + string.Join(",", criteriaRange1) + ", " + string.Join(",", criteria1) + ", " + string.Join(",", criteriaRange2) + ", " + string.Join(",", criteria2) + ")");
}

// Example usage:
double[] values = {10, 20, 30};
string[] criteria1 = {"A", "B", "A"};
string[] criteria2 = {"X", "Y", "X"};
double sum = SumValuesBasedOnCriteria(values, criteria1, "A", criteria2, "X"); // Sums values where criteria1 is "A" and criteria2 is "X"
```

The ABS function in Syncfusion WinForms can be used to calculate the absolute value of a number. Here's an example of how to use it in a C# application:

