The COUNT function in Syncfusion WinForms is used to count the number of non-empty cells in a dataset. It ignores empty cells and only counts cells that contain values. Here's an example of how to use it:

```csharp
using Syncfusion.Windows.Forms.Calculate;

// Create an instance of the CalculateEngine
var engine = new CalculateEngine();

// Define a range of values
var values = new object[] { 10, null, 20, 30, null };

// Use the COUNT function
var count = engine.Evaluate("COUNT(" + string.Join(",", values) + ")");

// Output the result
Console.WriteLine("Count of non-empty cells: " + count); // Output: 3
```
In this example, the COUNT function evaluates the number of non-null values in the array, ignoring the empty cells.

